OL,3,CPolice Ombudsman to appeal High Court
OL,4,Cruling that office exceeded powers
OL,6,F"She is appointed by the Executive
OL,7,FOffice acting jointly and to the best
OL,8,Fof my knowledge, the Department of
OL,9,FJustice has no powers to remove or
OL,10,Fdislodge the Ombudsman from office
OL,11,Fonce appointed by the Executive
OL,12,FOffice."
OL,14,FLeader of the Opposition Matthew
OL,15,FO'Toole said: "Speaker, for the record
OL,16,Fand in contrast to some of the
OL,17,Fchuntering we're hearing in the
OL,18,Fchamber today, it's worth putting on
OL,19,Fthe record.
